HEADWORD: Warburgs tincture
<hw>War"burg's tinc"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Pharm.)</fld> <def>A
preparation containing quinine and many other ingredients, often used in
the treatment of malarial affections. It was invented by Dr.
<ets>Warburg</ets> of London.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

